<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FAN DRIVE CLUTCH: KYSOR 1090 (8000 SERIES) - REASSEMBLE - INSTALL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Before putting the fan clutch in position, the fan may have to be put onto the front of the
                clutch or set into the shroud.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">DO NOT PERMANENTLY MOUNT THE FAN TO THE CLUTCH UNTIL THE CLUTCH IS MOUNTED TO THE
                    HUB.
                </emph>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount the fan clutch to the hub, using the self-locking 3/8-16 socket head capscrews that
                are 1.00" longer than the adapter for proper thread engagement. Torque to 44 ft-lbs. (60 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach the fan and make sure there is a 1-inch clearance on the front, 1/2-inch on the rear
                side of the fan blades, and that 3/4-inch tip clearance exists (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200114">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200114" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200114" filename="../figg12/G1200114.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Fan Clearance</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
